
/*
 * This Hyperlambda code snippet uses the [sleep] slot to pause the execution of the current thread for a specified duration. The duration is determined by the value of the [delay] node within the [.arguments] node set. The [sleep] slot effectively releases the thread back to the operating system, ensuring that the call is non-blocking and does not consume any physical operating system threads during the sleep period. 
 * 
 * 1. [sleep] - Pauses the execution for the duration specified by the [delay] node.
 * 2. [x:@.arguments/*/delay] - Retrieves the value of the [delay] node from the [.arguments] node set to determine the sleep duration.
 */
sleep:x:@.arguments/*/delay
